The article discusses a new Executive Order signed by President Obama called the BuySecure Initiative, which aims to improve financial security for consumers. The order includes measures such as using microchips in payment cards instead of magnetic strips, implementing PINs for cards, and promoting stronger security technologies. The President also announced the White House Summit on Cybersecurity and Consumer Protection to promote partnership and innovation in protecting consumer financial data. The article also highlights efforts by the government and private sector to improve security, such as companies like Home Depot, Target, Walgreens, and Walmart rolling out secure chip and PIN-compatible card terminals in their stores. The article emphasizes the need for Congress to pass data breach and cybersecurity legislation to address the increasing threat of cybercrime.